# STEP 2 — VERIFY NATURAL STP ELECTION

# No priorities configured yet

Run on all switches:

```cisco id="u4b2n8"
show spanning-tree vlan 1
show spanning-tree vlan 10
show spanning-tree summary
```

━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━

# EXPECTED RESULT

* Switch with lowest MAC address becomes Root Bridge
* One redundant path enters blocking state
* STP prevents Layer 2 loop

━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━

# IDENTIFY BLOCKED PORTS

Run:

```cisco id="f9z3p6"
show spanning-tree vlan 1
```

Look for:

```text id="w6v2j4"
Role = Alternate
State = Blocking
```

Document:

* Root Bridge
* Root Ports
* Designated Ports
* Blocked Ports

━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━

# PHASE 3 — FORCE ROOT BRIDGE MANUALLY

# Make S1 the Root Primary

━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━

## S1

```cisco id="n8x5m2"
configure terminal

spanning-tree vlan 1 root primary
spanning-tree vlan 10 root primary

end
write memory
```

━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━

# Configure Backup Root

## S2

```cisco id="r3k7t1"
configure terminal

spanning-tree vlan 1 root secondary
spanning-tree vlan 10 root secondary

end
write memory
```

